    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I recently saw the <a href="http://www.ikeahackers.net/2010/12/ikeapad-stand.html">IKEAPad stand</a> on <a href="http://www.ikeahackers.net/">IKEA Hackers</a> and I really liked it. <a href="http://www.ikeahackers.net/2010/12/ikeapad-stand.html">IKEAPad</a> is basically a simple iPad stand constructed from an <a href="http://www.ikea.com/us/en/catalog/products/76696009/">Ekby Valter</a> that costs 3$, that is less cheaper that you would pay for any iPad stand on the market. After reading the article, I decided to create my own version, for this you will need to buy 2 pieces of Ekby Valter and take out the shortest piece of wood from one of the Ekby Valter and use it as a dowel. I guess it is easier to understand if you see it.</p>

